<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Hague,
                                        The Netherlands</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-15"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 6 (Luxemburg series).</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a
                                note<note n="a" xml:id="d199fna">Not printed.</note> from His Royal
                            Highness the Grand Duke of Luxemburg, together with office copy of the
                            same, to the President announcing the death of His Royal Highness the
                            Grand Duke Adolpho and the accession of the Grand Duke William to the
                            Throne of the Grand Duchy of Luxemburg.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>